== Sesame-Sriracha-Soy Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @scallion whites{} from @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), @white wine vinegar{1 1/2%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{}; set aside to pickle.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoons}, @sugar{1%tablespoon}, and up to @sriracha{1%teaspoon} (save any remaining for serving).

== Rice ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @ginger{1%thumb}(peeled and minced or grated) and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3%ounce}, 1 1/2 cups water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> Save jasmine rice for another use. You will also microwave the cauliflower rice separately.

Place @riced cauliflower{12%ounce} in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{} (use a large bowl for 4 servings). Stir in ginger, @butter{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cover bowl tightly with #plastic wrap{} and poke a few holes in wrap.

Microwave until tender, ~{5%minutes}. Set aside.

== Vegetables ==

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Peel and mince or grate ginger. Trim and thinly slice scallions, separating whites from greens. Trim and peel @carrot{3%ounce}. Using a #peeler{}, shave carrot lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the core. Discard core.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise) lengthwise; cut crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons.

Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add carrot and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Add zucchini and another drizzle of oil to pan. Cook, stirring, until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl with carrot.

Add mushrooms and another drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} to pan. Cook, stirring, until tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to bowl with veggies. Wipe out pan.

== Fried Egg ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoons} in pan used for veggies over medium heat. Once hot, crack @eggs{2} into pan and cover. (For 4 servings, you may want to cook eggs in batches.) Fry eggs to preference. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Arrange carrot, zucchini, and mushrooms on top. Top each bowl with a fried egg and pickled scallion whites (draining first). Drizzle with sauce and any remaining Sriracha to taste. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.